// Man page for and
manAnd="AND(1)                           X Shell Manual                           AND(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    command ; command - Execute multiple commands unconditionally
    command && command - Execute commands conditionally

<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Two ways to chain commands together:

    <b>Semicolon (;)</b>
    Execute commands sequentially, one after another, regardless of
    success or failure. All commands run in order.

    <b>Logical AND (&&)</b>
    Execute commands conditionally. The second command only runs if
    the first command succeeds (returns non-error result).

<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Unconditional Chaining</color>
    <b>ls ; pwd ; whoami</b>
    Run three commands in sequence

    <b>cd /home/tux ; touch file.txt ; ls</b>
    Change directory, create file, list contents

    <color=#e4ff34># Conditional Chaining</color>
    <b>cd /etc && ls</b>
    Only list contents if cd succeeds

    <b>gzip -c -f secret.txt && rm secret.txt</b>
    Only delete original if compression succeeds

    <b>nmap -l && show</b>
    Only show results if scan succeeds

    <b>scan -l -p 22 && libssh</b>
    Only run libssh if port 22 is open

    <color=#e4ff34># Mixed Chaining</color>
    <b>cd /etc && cat passwd ; echo done</b>
    cd and cat are conditional, echo runs regardless"